Just in case you need a reminder to slow down a little, here it is 🤍 You deserve to do more than wake up, work, stress out, go to bed and repeat that all over again tomorrow. 

Last Friday I had a complete breakdown that looking back on my early 20s, all I will be able to think about when I think about this time in my life is …. I worked. A lot. In a normal day I have my laptop open from 6am to 8pm. I’m exhausted all day everyday. Burnt out doesn’t even cover it. 

I’m not posting this for pity or for sympathy, but to keep myself accountable on forcing rest into my day, daily, and to challenge you all to do the same. 

Your mental health matters. You matter. 🫶🏽

Have you thought about how you’re going to spend the night before your wedding day? 🥰

Planning some alone time with your partner before your big day gives you the chance to take a breather and hang together before you’re likely to be apart or around your community for a good amount of the next day 🙌

I’ve seen couples spend the night together, have a date night before parting ways for bed, go out to a nice place for dinner and drinks or head to their favorite beach for sunset 🤌 the possibilities are endless! 

These two wanted to traipse around their hotel and get a little steamy with it 😎🔥 (pro tip: I’m ALWAYS down to run away for a few minutes on your big day for a steamy flash session 🔥)

THE NIGHT BEFORE 🫶🏽

The night before our wedding was everything we could ask for and more! Ryley’s parents, Amy & Nick, planned an incredible welcome party for ALL of our guests to enjoy the day before. 

If you’re doing a destination wedding, I 10/10 recommend a welcome party over a traditional rehearsal dinner! ✨

If you’re looking for incredible photographers, that travel literally across the country (California to South Carolina), I cannot recommend @capturedbyamandalynn enough. Amanda & KC are the absolute best!! SO many people have asked for their information since the wedding, because they were seriously incredible. 🥰

Also, DO a night before the wedding shoot. It was so much freaking fun 👏🏽

The best year of my life is coming to an end, and I am SO thankful it’s not even funny

1. Married my BEST FRIEND on our favorite islands, surrounded by 120 of our closest friends and family. 💍
2. Traveled to Hilton Head Island, South Carolina 3 times 🌴
3. Had the prettiest bridal shower a girl could ever dream of ✨
4. Had the best bachelorette party in Nashville with all my best friends! 🩷
5. Went to Hawaii for the most boujee honeymoon and it was the best decision EVER ☀️
6. Went to tons of concerts with my best friend and got to watch her GLOW through her entire pregnancy 🥰
7. SOLD our home and moved back to my hometown to be close to my family! 🏡
8. Found out WE ARE PREGNANT when a baby girl, due in June 👶🏻
9. Got to meet my besties baby boy 🥹
10. Purchased my first home with my husband, a fixer upper, to bring our baby girl home in 🏠

Closing out the best year of our lives and welcoming the year we become parents! My biggest dreams are coming true, and I am forever thankful for all that 2023 brought. Bring on 2024, the year we welcome a baby girl to our world 🩷🥰

I feel like I’ve been holding my breath waiting to hit 16 weeks, and here we are 🥹 Baby girl is the size of an avocado 🥑 

This week:
- I felt baby girl move for the first time
- Had a full appetite 
- Still down from pre pregnancy weight 
- Took less naps and feel more energized 
- Experienced too much vertigo for my own comfort lol
